column59: Behaviour description

Diva was well behaved during this exercise with only one hind-quarter shuffle. But from her fixation on the kong, and un-diverted attention (apart from one gaze away) she was clearly very interested in it.
settled. reminded once to sit, looked away twice
Kept seated, didnt shuffle, looks away for a time, and though he seems fixated I think he is more waiting on handler to make next move rather than having and very high interest over the kong
stayed sitting

moved once, looked away once
tail waging, lifts hind quarters and mouths and then at the end jumps up at handler.
generally sitting but towards the end he jumps up to get the kong

High level of excitement. Jumps up immediately and then once by breaking his sit. His tail is constantly wagging and he is showing anxiety over wanting the toy including lip smacking and shifting weight.

barks at handler, unsettled sit

dog sit but moves slightly
